Provides an Elastic Container Registry Pull Through Cache Rule.

More information about pull through cache rules, including the set of supported
upstream repositories, see [Using pull through cache rules](https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonECR/latest/userguide/pull-through-cache.html).

        <span id="ecrrepositoryprefix_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#ecrrepositoryprefix_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Ecr<wbr>Repository<wbr>Prefix</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The repository name prefix to use when caching images from the source registry. Use <code>ROOT</code> as the prefix to apply a template to all repositories in your registry that don't have an associated pull through cache rule.</dd><dt class="property-required property-replacement"
            title="Required">
        <span id="upstreamregistryurl_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#upstreamregistryurl_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Upstream<wbr>Registry<wbr>Url</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The registry URL of the upstream registry to use as the source.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="credentialarn_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#credentialarn_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Credential<wbr>Arn</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>ARN of the Secret which will be used to authenticate against the registry.</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="customrolearn_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#customrolearn_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Custom<wbr>Role<wbr>Arn</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The ARN of the IAM role associated with the pull through cache rule. Must be specified if the upstream registry is a cross-account ECR private registry. See <a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonECR/latest/userguide/pull-through-cache-private.html">AWS Document - Setting up permissions for cross-account ECR to ECR PTC</a>.</dd><dt class="property-optional property-replacement"
            title="Optional">
        <span id="upstreamrepositoryprefix_csharp">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#upstreamrepositoryprefix_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Upstream<wbr>Repository<wbr>Prefix</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The upstream repository prefix associated with the pull through cache rule. Used if the upstream registry is an ECR private registry. If not specified, it's set to <code>ROOT</code>, which allows matching with any upstream repository. See <a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonECR/latest/userguide/pull-through-cache-private-wildcards.html">AWS Document - Customizing repository prefixes for ECR to ECR pull through cache</a>.</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>

            title="Optional">
        <span id="state_ecrrepositoryprefix_csharp">

</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The repository name prefix to use when caching images from the source registry. Use <code>ROOT</code> as the prefix to apply a template to all repositories in your registry that don't have an associated pull through cache rule.</dd><dt class="property-optional"

<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#state_upstream_repository_prefix_python" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">upstream_<wbr>repository_<wbr>prefix</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">str</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>The upstream repository prefix associated with the pull through cache rule. Used if the upstream registry is an ECR private registry. If not specified, it's set to <code>ROOT</code>, which allows matching with any upstream repository. See <a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonECR/latest/userguide/pull-through-cache-private-wildcards.html">AWS Document - Customizing repository prefixes for ECR to ECR pull through cache</a>.</dd></dl>

## Import



Using `pulumi import`, import a pull-through cache rule using the `ecr_repository_prefix`. For example:

```sh
$ pulumi import aws:ecr/pullThroughCacheRule:PullThroughCacheRule example ecr-public
```


To learn more about importing existing cloud resources, see [Importing resources](/docs/using-pulumi/adopting-pulumi/import/).
